724559f-a.text:
(I) West Street, west side, north from Rector Street, showing North River Piers that line this water front street. The uniform row, consisting of Piers 8 and 11, inclusive (first bridge), are used by the Central Railroad of New Jersey. The pedestrian overpasses shown, enable individuals to cross this arterial thoroughfare safely to Liberty Street
Ferry and the Pennsylvania Company Ferry.
Photographers advantage point to 72 Washington Street.
September 20th, 1929
(2) The same, at a later period.
October 8th, 1938
Photographs by,
P.L.Sperr,
No Reproductions.
